The pair went on to have blood tests and against all the odds, they showed that Ray was a match - despite not being related.

The successful transplant went ahead at London’s Great Ormond Street Hospital in February.

Both Alya and Mr Coe are now recovering well from the operation and are expected to return to school after the Easter break.

Mr Coe said: 'For her parents, it’s not words that can express their gratitude. For them, I have saved their daughter’s life.

