'It’s like I am another family member now.'

Alya’s father, Ahmed Ali, 47, has hailed Mr Coe a 'hero and a lifesaver'.

He said: 'Ray has given Alya much more than just the gift of life. He’s an amazing man, we owe him so much.'

School headteacher Wendy Bower said: 'Mr Coe has gone above and beyond the call of duty with this selfless and noble act.

'He is a very humble and modest man. The whole staff are in admiration for his kindness. He has given a new life to Alya and her whole family.'

